About Me

Entry-level cybersecurity fresher currently pursuing a B.Sc. in Information Technology, with a strong interest in cybersecurity and information security. Gaining foundational knowledge through academic coursework, guided labs, projects, and simulated industry environments while completing graduation.

Hands-on exposure to information security fundamentals, basic incident analysis, digital forensics concepts, network security principles, and secure system design as part of learning activities. Practiced using Python and PowerShell to build small security tools and automation scripts with the support of GitHub Copilot and AI-assisted development tools, along with Nmap and common security workflows for academic and lab-based security tasks. Familiar with introductory concepts related to endpoint threats, password security, encryption, access control, and working in Windows and Linux environments, with basic awareness of cloud security concepts.

CompTIA Security+ certified, with a foundational understanding of security concepts aligned to MITRE ATT&CK. Seeking an entry-level cybersecurity or information security role where I can apply learned concepts, continue developing technical skills, and gain hands-on experience in real-world security operations under guidance and mentorship.
